        <!-- ARTICLE on Cedric Diggory's Life -->
        <article>
            <h2>One of my favorite character: Cedric Diggory</h2>
            <div><em><strong>While the series primarily focuses on Harry, the expansive universe Rowling built is filled with numerous intriguing characters. One such character, who made a significant impact despite his brief appearance, is Cedric Diggory.</em></strong></div>
            <img src="images/ceddd.jpg" alt="Description of image 2">

            <h3>Cedric Diggory's Early Life</h3>
            <p>Cedric Diggory hailed from a wizarding family known for its honorable lineage. The Diggorys, though not as famous as the Potters or the Weasleys, had a legacy at Hogwarts, primarily associated with the House of Hufflepuff. A tall young man with a striking presence, Cedric's deep-set gray eyes and wavy hair made him stand out in a crowd. Attending Hogwarts, he was sorted into Hufflepuff. It's during his time here that Cedric showcased qualities like fairness, bravery, and determination, which endeared him to many, including Professor Sprout, the head of Hufflepuff House.</p>
            <h3>Triwizard Tournament: Cedric's Finest Hour</h3>
            <p>The Triwizard Tournament was an event that tested young witches and wizards beyond their limits. When the Goblet of Fire spit out Cedric's name as one of the champions, many were surprised, but those who knew him had faith in his capabilities. Cedric's participation in the Triwizard Tournament wasn't without its challenges. From retrieving a golden egg from a dragon to navigating a maze filled with dangerous creatures, he displayed immense courage and intellect.</p>
            <br>
            <div><em><strong>He successfully retrieved the egg, Rescued all hostages on time, and reached the Triwizard Cup with Harry. </strong></em></div>
